From: Olekhov Vasilii <olekhov@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 16 May 2026 18:30:00 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] ath79: dts: gl-e750: declare toggle switch as EV_SW

The GL.iNet GL-E750 exposes its hardware side switch as a gpio-keys
input with code BTN_0, but without an explicit linux,input-type.

gpio-button-hotplug defaults such inputs to EV_KEY. That is good enough
for momentary buttons, but it is not the correct model for a latching
hardware switch. In practice this prevents userland from reliably
treating the control as a switch with an initial state.

Mark the "switch" GPIO as EV_SW so OpenWrt reports it as a switch-type
button hotplug event. This aligns GL-E750 with other OpenWrt devices
that expose physical mode/VPN sliders through gpio-button-hotplug.

Signed-off-by: Olekhov Vasilii <olekhov@gmail.com>
---
 target/linux/ath79/dts/qca9531_glinet_gl-e750.dts | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/target/linux/ath79/dts/qca9531_glinet_gl-e750.dts b/target/linux/ath79/dts/qca9531_glinet_gl-e750.dts
index xxxxxxx..xxxxxxx 100644
--- a/target/linux/ath79/dts/qca9531_glinet_gl-e750.dts
+++ b/target/linux/ath79/dts/qca9531_glinet_gl-e750.dts
@@ -28,6 +28,7 @@
 		switch {
 			label = "switch";
 			linux,code = <BTN_0>;
+			linux,input-type = <EV_SW>;
 			gpios = <&gpio 1 GPIO_ACTIVE_LOW>;
 		};
 	};
